<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FDD3BA0DFD764165" box="[595,645,1292,1319]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">16C</figureCitation>
). Body light pink in life (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FC1ABA0DFC0C4165" box="[922,1023,1292,1319]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-50@21.[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). A—dorsal view. B—ventral view. C—dorsal view of anterior, live. D—parapodia. E—drawing of compound chaetae. F—compound chaetae. G—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479949/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 15C</figureCitation>
). Body brown/orange with numerous dark pigmentation speckles in preserved (formalin/ethanol) state (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FC0CBA31FBE94109" box="[908,1050,1328,1355]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-50@21.[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). A—dorsal view. B—ventral view. C—dorsal view of anterior, live. D—parapodia. E—drawing of compound chaetae. F—compound chaetae. G—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479949/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 15A, B</figureCitation>
). Prostomium slightly wider than long; nuchal organs not visible (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FE7FBA55FD7A412D" box="[511,649,1364,1391]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16A, D</figureCitation>
). Anterior dorsal edge of prostomium with paired cylindrical antennae ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1F4B30FF25BA79FEFF41D1" box="[165,268,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FED8BA79FE3141D1" box="[344,450,1400,1427]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
). Paired palps ventral to antennae, similar in shape and length to antennae (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FAA5BA79FA6341D1" box="[1317,1424,1400,1427]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
). Segment 1 fused to prostomium, following segments clearly demarcated (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FC5ABA9DFBB041F5" box="[986,1091,1436,1463]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
). Pair of elongated dorsal cirri [tentacular cirri] on each of segments 1 (~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1F4B30FDFDBAC1FD244199" box="[637,727,1472,1499]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long), 2 (~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1F4B30FCD9BAC1FC314199" box="[857,962,1472,1499]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.42">0.42 mm</quantity>
long) and 3 (~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1F4B30FBEFBAC1FB2B4199" box="[1135,1240,1472,1499]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.44">0.44 mm</quantity>
long) (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FAAEBAC1FF5C41BD" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16A, D</figureCitation>
). All elongated dorsal cirri cirriform, tapering distally. Ventral cirri absent from segment 1 (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FB4EBAE5FACA41BD" box="[1230,1337,1508,1535]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
). Pair of elongated ventral cirri on segment 2 ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1F4B30FDC5B909FD6E4261" box="[581,669,1544,1571]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FD66B909FCA34261" box="[742,848,1544,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
). Bulbous, rounded dorsal cirri ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1F4B30FB46B909FAEE4261" box="[1222,1309,1544,1571]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long begin on segment 3 continuing posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FDBCB92DFD504205" box="[572,675,1580,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16C</figureCitation>
). Cylindrical, tapering ventral cirri ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1F4B30FBC0B92DFB654205" box="[1088,1174,1580,1607]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long begin on segment 3 continuing posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FE3CB951FDD44229" box="[444,551,1616,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
). Parapodia uniramous, notopodial chaetae absent; neuropodium with central fascicle containing ~5–9 compound chaetae; one simple emergent acicula (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FC65B975FB4342CC" box="[997,1200,1652,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-50@21.[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). A—dorsal view. B—ventral view. C—dorsal view of anterior, live. D—parapodia. E—drawing of compound chaetae. F—compound chaetae. G—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479949/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Figs 15D, E, F, G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FB3CB975FAF842CD" box="[1212,1291,1652,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure-25@22.[164,1423,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Scanning electron microscopy (SEM) of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp.A—close-up dorsal view of anterior and prostomium, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). B—ventral view of pygidium (pygidial cirri broke off, two scars seen at distal end), paratype (SIO-BIC A4590). C—dorsal view of anterior, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). D—ventral view of anterior (tips of antennae and palps broken off), holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). E—compound chaetae, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). F—parapodia, holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). Abbreviations: a, antennae; bo, buccal organ; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium; pyg, pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479951" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479951/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">16E, F</figureCitation>
). Compound chaetal shaft cylindrical; thin, flattened pointed blade extended from curved joint (
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FBB2B999FB6442F1" box="[1074,1175,1688,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetId="figure-50@21.[164,1423,237,1866]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 15. Light microscopy (LM) images of Galapagomystides bobpearsoni n. sp. holotype (SIO-BIC A4588). A—dorsal view. B—ventral view. C—dorsal view of anterior, live. D—parapodia. E—drawing of compound chaetae. F—compound chaetae. G—compound chaetae. Abbreviations: a, antennae; dc, dorsal cirri; edc, elongated dorsal cirri; evc, elongated ventral cirri; vc, ventral cirri; p, palps; pro, prostomium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479949/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 15E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1032A7733C1F4B30FF47B9BDFBE142B8" blockId="20.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FF47B9BDFECC4294" bold="true" box="[199,319,1724,1750]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Variation.</emphasis>
Only 
<specimenCount id="068B6CFA3C1F4B30FE04B9BCFDD94294" box="[388,554,1724,1751]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
were collected. The 
<typeStatus id="CF3619D13C1F4B30FC91B9BCFC824295" box="[785,881,1725,1751]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">paratype</typeStatus>
matches the 
<typeStatus id="CF3619D13C1F4B30FB83B9BDFB9B4294" box="[1027,1128,1724,1750]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">holotype</typeStatus>
, but is also complete with a pygidium, which has a pair of small lobed cirri ~ 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1F4B30FD39B9E1FCE342B9" box="[697,784,1760,1787]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
long, rounded distally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5897F4F83C1F4B30FF47B805FB5643B4" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1032A7733C1F4B30FF47B805FB5643B4" blockId="20.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FF47B805FEC8435C" bold="true" box="[199,315,1796,1822]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FEC4B805FD5A435C" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[324,681,1796,1822]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FEC4B805FD5A435C" box="[324,681,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Galapagomystides bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1F4B30FD32B804FD1C435D" box="[690,751,1797,1823]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically like 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FB88B805FB70435C" authorityName=", Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[1032,1155,1796,1822]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aristata">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FB88B805FB70435C" box="[1032,1155,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. aristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FB3CB805FAC4435C" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[1212,1335,1796,1822]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FB3CB805FAC4435C" box="[1212,1335,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1F4B30FAC0B804FA8D435D" box="[1344,1406,1797,1823]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having segment 1 dorsally fused to the prostomium. However, in the phylogenetic analyses 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FB28B829FAA44300" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[1192,1367,1832,1858]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FB28B829FAA44300" box="[1192,1367,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1F4B30FADFB828FA6F4301" box="[1375,1436,1833,1859]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was found to be the sister group to a clade comprising 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FD7FB84DFC8A4324" authorityName=", Blake" authorityYear="1985" box="[767,889,1868,1894]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="aristata">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FD7FB84DFC8A4324" box="[767,889,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. aristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FC07B84DFBF24324" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[903,1025,1868,1894]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kathyae" status="n. sp. and g.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FC07B84DFBF24324" box="[903,1025,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. kathyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1F4B30FB89B84CFB644324" box="[1033,1175,1868,1895]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="genus">
n. sp. and 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FBFCB84DFB644324" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Blake and Hilbig" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[1148,1175,1868,1894]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="verenae" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FBFCB84DFB644324" box="[1148,1175,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FB1FB84CFB044324" box="[1183,1271,1869,1894]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">verenae</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1F4B30FB7EB84CFA934324" box="[1278,1376,1868,1895]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="88B6BBF63C1F4B30FAEFB84DFF5543C8" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1907,1931]" captionTargetBox="[181,1408,279,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-61@7.[177,1411,273,1884]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Maximum Likelihood (ML) tree generated from the concatenation of mitochondrial (COI 16rRNA) and nuclear genes (18S rRNA, 28S rRNA). Numbers on nodes represent ML bootstrap values (above node) and Bayesian posterior probabilities (below node). Values below 50% for ML and 0.70 for posterior probabilities are not shown. ‘*’ indicates G. aristata as the type species of Galapagomystides." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479921/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FF39B871FDD243C8" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[185,545,1904,1930]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FF39B871FDD243C8" box="[185,545,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Galapagomystides bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1F4B30FDACB870FD9F43C9" box="[556,620,1905,1931]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is restricted to Lau Back-arc Basin between 
<quantity id="D7750A963C1F4B30FB02B871FAD243C9" box="[1154,1313,1904,1931]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.305" metricValueMax="2.7199999999999998" metricValueMin="1.89" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" unit="m" value="2305.0" valueMax="2720.0" valueMin="1890.0">1890–2720 m</quantity>
depth. An obvious morphological feature distinguishing 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FD1AB895FCBB43EC" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[666,840,1940,1966]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FD1AB895FCBB43EC" box="[666,840,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1F4B30FCCEB894FC7943ED" box="[846,906,1941,1967]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the very long cirriform elongated dorsal cirri originating from the first three segments, the longest projecting from segments two and three. The chaetal blades of 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FF17B8DDFEB643B4" authority="Pearson &amp; Rouse, 2022" authorityName="Pearson &amp; Rouse" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,325,2012,2038]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="bobpearsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FF17B8DDFEB643B4" box="[151,325,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">G. bobpearsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="39CAC61A3C1F4B30FECCB8DCFE7B43B5" box="[332,392,2013,2039]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are also notable for being the longest of all 
<taxonomicName id="D78DDCF03C1F4B30FCF5B8DDFB5643B4" box="[885,1189,2012,2038]" class="Polychaeta" family="Phyllodocidae" genus="Galapagomystides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undefined-A">
<emphasis id="22F97B613C1F4B30FCF5B8DDFBB643B4" box="[885,1093,2012,2038]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Galapagomystides</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
